        "text": "Regional tau burden is a stronger predictor of near-term cognitive decline in Alzheimer's patients than regional amyloid burden. Predictions: In a longitudinal cohort with both tau-PET and amyloid-PET at baseline, tau-PET SUVR will explain significantly more variance in 12-month change on cognitive composites (e.g., MMSE, ADAS-Cog) than amyloid-PET SUVR.; Patients amyloid-positive but tau-negative will show slower cognitive decline than tau-positive patients matched on amyloid burden.",
